        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): show actionable error feedback when config.openFile fails",
        "body": "Fixes #87020\n\n## Problem\nControl UI shows no actionable feedback when `config.openFile` fails in a headless VPS environment:\n- xdg-open fails with \"no method available\" error\n- UI shows no error message to user\n- Users may think the Control UI is broken\n\n## Solution\n\n### 1. Server Side Improvement\nEnhanced error handling in `config.openFile` handler:\n- Detect headless environment errors (`xdg-open` + `no method available`)\n- Provide detailed, actionable error message:\n  - \"Cannot open file in headless environment\"\n  - File path included\n  - Explanation of missing browser handler\n\n### 2. Client Side Improvement\nEnhanced `openConfigFile` in Control UI:\n- Check response `{ ok: false }` properly\n- Display error message via `state.lastError`\n- Copy file path to clipboard as fallback\n- Show actionable feedback to users\n\n## Changes\n- `src/gateway/server-methods/config.ts`: Improved error message formatting\n- `ui/src/ui/controllers/config.ts`: Handle ok=false response properly\n\n## Testing\nManual verification of error detection logic.\n\n## Expected Behavior After Fix\nWhen `config.openFile` fails in headless VPS:\n1. UI shows error message\n2. File path copied to clipboard automatically\n3. User knows exactly what happened and has workaround",
